qas.question: What countries led the two coalitions during the Seven Years' War?

answers.text: two coalitions, led by Great Britain on one side and France

qas.question: When was the Seven Year' War fought?

answers.text: The Seven Years' War was fought between 1755 and 1764

qas.question: What major power of the time was not involved in The Seven Years' War?

answers.text: It involved every great power of the time except the Ottoman Empire

qas.question: What country emerged as the world's predominate power?

answers.text: Britain rose as the world's predominant power

qas.question: What was the Seven Years' War considered as the prelude to?

answers.text: Considered a prelude to the two world wars

context: <a1_0>The Seven Years' War was fought between 1755 and 1764<a1_0/>, the main conflict occurring in the seven-year period from 1756 to 1763. <a2_0>It involved every great power of the time except the Ottoman Empire<a2_0/>, and affected Europe, the Americas, West Africa, India, and the Philippines. <a4_0>Considered a prelude to the two world wars<a4_0/> and the greatest European war since the Thirty Years War of the 17th century, it once again split Europe into <a0_0>two coalitions, led by Great Britain on one side and France<a0_0/> on the other. For the first time, aiming to curtail Britain and Prussia's ever-growing might, France formed a grand coalition of its own, which ended with failure as <a3_0>Britain rose as the world's predominant power<a3_0/>, altering the European balance of power.
